WEBVTT

00:00.779 --> 00:03.651
(screaming)

00:05.454 --> 00:08.494
♪ ♪

00:25.695 --> 00:27.732
♪ ♪

00:56.389 --> 00:59.562
("#1 Crush" by Garbage playing)

01:01.567 --> 01:05.709
♪ Ah-ah, ah, ah, ah ♪

01:05.742 --> 01:08.146
-♪ I would die for you ♪
-♪ Ah-ah ♪

01:08.179 --> 01:10.852
-♪ I would die for you ♪
-♪ Ah, ah, ah ♪

01:10.885 --> 01:13.825
-♪ I've been dying just to ♪
-♪ Ah-ah, ah ♪

01:13.858 --> 01:17.431
-♪ Feel you by my side ♪
-♪ Ah ♪

01:17.464 --> 01:19.770
♪ Ah-ah, ah, ah, ah ♪

01:19.803 --> 01:23.376
♪ To know that you're mine ♪

01:24.445 --> 01:29.556
♪ Ah-ah, ah, ah, ah ♪

01:29.589 --> 01:33.564
♪ Ah-ah, ah, ah ♪

01:33.597 --> 01:36.202
♪ I would die for you. ♪

01:42.615 --> 01:44.653
(solemn organ music playing)

02:02.756 --> 02:03.958
-Sam?
-Hmm?

02:03.991 --> 02:06.463
A quick word?

02:06.497 --> 02:08.634
Three hours all in?

02:08.667 --> 02:10.270
I did it in two.

02:10.303 --> 02:12.475
She was in bad shape
when she came in.

02:12.509 --> 02:14.479
Good work.

02:14.513 --> 02:16.884
Oh, are we having a moment?

02:16.917 --> 02:19.690
When you first started here, I
didn't think you'd last a week.

02:19.723 --> 02:22.228
Yeah, and now,
what would you do without me?

02:22.261 --> 02:23.865
-Yeah.
-I mean, you don't pay me
nearly enough,

02:23.898 --> 02:27.672
but, um, you're lucky I do it
for the love of the game.

02:27.705 --> 02:29.275
(Sam laughs softly)

02:29.308 --> 02:32.348
I can see that... in the work.

02:32.381 --> 02:34.853
You actually care.

02:34.886 --> 02:39.797
I think that deserves a raise.

02:39.830 --> 02:43.604
Um, uh, thank you.

02:43.637 --> 02:45.274
Yeah. I-I do care.

02:45.307 --> 02:48.714
I-I believe what we do here
is very special.

02:48.747 --> 02:50.384
Keep your head in the game, Sam.

02:50.417 --> 02:51.887
You've got a bright future here.

02:51.920 --> 02:53.957
-Thank you.
-(chuckles softly)

02:55.661 --> 02:58.568
♪ ♪

02:58.601 --> 03:00.638
Jesse?

03:01.940 --> 03:03.977
Jesse?!

03:05.648 --> 03:06.784
Hey, you.

03:06.817 --> 03:08.754
-Hi.
-Missed you last night.

03:08.787 --> 03:11.594
I'm sorry.
I wish you could've seen it.

03:11.627 --> 03:14.900
The family thanked me.
God, it was so emotional.

03:14.933 --> 03:18.306
Even Henderson had to admit that
I did a great job, and then...

03:19.709 --> 03:21.647
-...he offered me a raise.
-Hmm.

03:21.680 --> 03:23.751
-Mm.
-Hmm?

03:25.387 --> 03:26.757
It sounds like
you had a good day.

03:26.790 --> 03:28.761
Mm-hmm.

03:28.794 --> 03:30.932
You'll have to tell me
all about it tonight.

03:30.965 --> 03:33.336
-I got to go.
I'm late for court.
-No.

03:33.369 --> 03:35.407
Come on, Counselor.

03:35.440 --> 03:37.411
You can be
a couple minutes late.

03:37.444 --> 03:39.415
JESSE:
Mmm.

03:39.448 --> 03:42.354
Mm, sometimes it's fun
to go off script.

03:43.858 --> 03:46.462
Maybe the universe
will surprise you.

03:49.536 --> 03:52.007
I've got people depending on me.

03:52.040 --> 03:55.682
Victims to avenge,
criminals to put away.

03:55.715 --> 03:58.554
Okay, well,
go save the world or whatever.

04:00.858 --> 04:05.033
Why don't you...
go take a nice hot bath

04:05.066 --> 04:08.741
with some of that fancy
lavender oil I got you?

04:08.774 --> 04:11.780
Showered twice
before I left work, but...

04:12.916 --> 04:16.089
Maybe it's just my, uh,
extra sensitive sinuses,

04:16.122 --> 04:19.730
but that formaldehyde smell
is really something.

04:19.763 --> 04:21.366
-Bye.
-(door opens)

04:21.399 --> 04:23.370
See you later, babe.

04:23.403 --> 04:25.440
(door closes)

04:29.415 --> 04:31.553
♪ ♪

04:58.507 --> 05:01.680
♪ ♪

05:13.837 --> 05:16.644
Look, you probably smelled
like bacon and death.

05:16.677 --> 05:18.948
-Nobody wants to fuck that.
-(sighs) No, I...

05:18.981 --> 05:21.119
-It all just felt kind of weird.
-(laughs)

05:21.152 --> 05:24.458
Yeah, it's weird. (laughs)
If a guy turns down sex,

05:24.492 --> 05:26.029
-something is seriously wrong.
-SAM: Oh, I don't know.

05:26.062 --> 05:28.099
Even when we do have sex,
it's just like...

05:28.132 --> 05:31.907
something's... missing.

05:31.940 --> 05:33.443
It's just something off.

05:33.476 --> 05:34.780
It's-it's like
we're on separate tracks,

05:34.813 --> 05:36.449
heading in different directions.

05:36.482 --> 05:39.690
And, like, he won't
exactly say it, but I know

05:39.723 --> 05:41.493
he doesn't like me working
at the funeral home.

05:41.526 --> 05:43.664
And sometimes I just wonder
if he even gets me at all.

05:43.697 --> 05:47.037
Girl, you talk
to dead people, literally.

05:47.070 --> 05:49.509
-Relationships are
about compromise.
-(laughter)

05:49.542 --> 05:50.878
Nothing's perfect.

05:50.911 --> 05:52.515
Like, what have you done
for Jesse lately?

05:52.548 --> 05:53.918
I, uh... (laughs)

05:53.951 --> 05:55.822
I do the dishes. Sometimes.

05:55.855 --> 05:57.391
Mm.

05:57.424 --> 05:58.894
Laundry. When I remember.

05:58.927 --> 06:01.533
I drove ten minutes
out of the way

06:01.566 --> 06:03.571
the other day
to get his favorite ice cream.

06:03.604 --> 06:05.107
-DANI: Wow.
-Cool.

06:05.140 --> 06:07.111
If Jesse asked you, point blank,

06:07.144 --> 06:11.019
"Either the job's
got to go, or I do,"

06:11.052 --> 06:13.089
which would you pick?

06:14.526 --> 06:16.497
Uh-oh.

06:16.530 --> 06:18.768
You hesitated. Poor Jesse.

06:18.801 --> 06:20.805
No, no. It's just, it's...

06:20.838 --> 06:22.776
It's complicated.

06:22.809 --> 06:24.746
What am I missing?

06:24.779 --> 06:27.184
I really love my job.

06:27.217 --> 06:28.754
And I'm good at it.

06:28.787 --> 06:31.092
And, uh, the deceased teach you

06:31.125 --> 06:32.896
something new every day.

06:32.929 --> 06:34.499
DANI:
How?

06:34.532 --> 06:36.069
They're dead.

06:36.102 --> 06:38.206
(laughs)

06:38.239 --> 06:40.077
See, that's the secret.

06:40.110 --> 06:44.018
People are the most interesting
right after death.

06:44.051 --> 06:45.722
(woman moans)

06:45.755 --> 06:47.993
One time,
this woman started moaning.

06:48.026 --> 06:50.665
Was she still alive?

06:50.698 --> 06:52.034
Totally dead.

06:52.067 --> 06:53.904
Gases-- they can build up
during decomposition,

06:53.937 --> 06:55.708
and when they try to escape,
sometimes it hits

06:55.741 --> 06:57.011
vocal cords
on the way out of the mouth.

06:57.044 --> 06:58.948
Sometimes the blood
rushes all the way down.

06:58.981 --> 07:00.952
A decedent will come in
with a boner.

07:00.985 --> 07:02.488
-JULES: Ew! Sam.
-(laughing)

07:02.522 --> 07:04.091
SAM:
The human body is insane.

07:04.124 --> 07:05.928
And we only understand
a small blip of what's actually

07:05.961 --> 07:08.601
happening inside,
so there's always

07:08.634 --> 07:09.903
something new to discover.

07:09.936 --> 07:12.575
But, okay, beyond that,

07:12.608 --> 07:15.147
I... I help people.

07:15.180 --> 07:17.886
I get to bring
their loved ones back to them,

07:17.919 --> 07:19.890
just for a little while.

07:19.923 --> 07:22.027
What I do is...
it's important.

07:23.162 --> 07:26.169
You just got more excited
talking about dead people

07:26.202 --> 07:28.974
than you've ever been
talking about Jesse.

07:29.007 --> 07:31.814
Maybe he's not the problem.

07:31.847 --> 07:34.185
SAM:
Yikes. What happened to you?

07:34.218 --> 07:36.890
Reginald Glover, 55 years old.

07:36.923 --> 07:40.765
Cause of death:
gunshot wound to the head.

07:40.798 --> 07:42.835
No kidding.

07:44.672 --> 07:47.846
Hi, Mr. Glover. I'm Sam.

07:47.879 --> 07:49.983
I'll be taking care
of you today.

07:50.016 --> 07:53.824
Looks like your family wants you
to have an open casket,

07:53.857 --> 07:56.129
so, I'm gonna need you
to work with me

07:56.162 --> 07:59.803
so we can make you look
presentable for your big day.

07:59.836 --> 08:02.307
I see you had six kids. Nice.

08:02.340 --> 08:05.013
Looks like they got you
the mahogany casket.

08:05.046 --> 08:07.050
That's our most expensive one.

08:07.083 --> 08:09.087
You must've been a good dad.

08:10.825 --> 08:15.167
And now...

08:15.200 --> 08:17.171
(door slams open)

08:17.204 --> 08:19.308
Uh, whoa. Hi. Um, sorry.

08:19.341 --> 08:20.945
What-what are you doing here?
This is a restricted area.

08:20.978 --> 08:23.049
Can you get out?

08:23.082 --> 08:25.788
I'm Charlie, the new grave
digger and death removal tech.

08:29.194 --> 08:30.998
Didn't mean to freak you out.

08:31.967 --> 08:33.938
Just tell me where to leave her.

08:33.971 --> 08:35.675
Um, just over there.

08:35.708 --> 08:37.845
I'll-I'll get to her
when I wrap up.

08:43.757 --> 08:46.095
(Charlie whispers)

08:53.911 --> 08:55.247
(door opens)

08:55.280 --> 08:57.585
(door closes)

09:14.318 --> 09:18.193
Hey, what did you say
down there to the decedent?

09:18.226 --> 09:20.263
I just thanked her.

09:20.296 --> 09:21.934
Thanked her for what?

09:21.967 --> 09:23.336
It's kind of private.

09:23.369 --> 09:25.675
Well, I'm-I'm sorry
I blew up on you.

09:25.708 --> 09:27.679
It's just, you weren't
supposed to be down there.

09:27.712 --> 09:30.584
I hear you. Won't happen again.

09:32.420 --> 09:34.391
I'm Sam.

09:34.424 --> 09:36.663
Nice to meet you, Sam.

09:39.702 --> 09:44.044
So, um, what's up
with the... the suit, the hat,

09:44.077 --> 09:46.048
-pimped-out ride?
-(laughs)

09:46.081 --> 09:48.353
Most, um,
body removal techs don't

09:48.386 --> 09:51.225
roll up with all
that pomp and circumstance.

09:51.258 --> 09:53.664
I think all of us deserve
to be sent off in style.

09:53.697 --> 09:57.137
I mean, who wants to ride into
the afterlife in a Kia Sorento?

09:57.170 --> 09:59.207
Fair enough.

10:03.884 --> 10:05.855
I thanked the decedent
for allowing me

10:05.888 --> 10:07.625
to escort her to you.

10:12.167 --> 10:14.238
Seriously?

10:14.271 --> 10:18.046
It's an honor to be a part
of someone's death journey.

10:18.079 --> 10:20.383
You know, in ancient Egypt,
only specialized priests,

10:20.416 --> 10:24.325
those handpicked by the gods,
were trusted to handle the dead.

10:24.358 --> 10:26.797
They'd spend up
to 70 days on one body,

10:26.830 --> 10:28.299
getting it ready
for the afterlife.

10:28.332 --> 10:30.369
I did know that.

10:32.407 --> 10:34.645
("Tessellations" by Jaguar Jones
playing)

10:39.021 --> 10:41.259
(water running)

10:41.292 --> 10:44.231
♪ Throw your knives, cut me ♪

10:44.264 --> 10:47.370
♪ Are we doing right? ♪

10:49.341 --> 10:51.780
♪ I need you
to tell me the softer ♪

10:51.813 --> 10:56.957
♪ The heavier parts
of your mind... ♪

10:56.990 --> 10:59.461
Wow.

10:59.495 --> 11:03.036
You look incredible.

11:03.069 --> 11:06.042
What's all this?

11:06.075 --> 11:08.413
Just wanted to look nice
for my guy.

11:08.446 --> 11:10.183
JESSE:
Mm.

11:10.216 --> 11:12.789
Thought maybe we could go...

11:12.822 --> 11:14.291
out to dinner?

11:14.324 --> 11:16.429
Mm-hmm.

11:16.462 --> 11:19.034
I think I'd rather stay in.

11:19.067 --> 11:21.104
Hmm? (laughs)

11:44.786 --> 11:48.727
(Jesse moaning)

11:52.835 --> 11:56.843
So, you believe
in the afterlife?

11:56.876 --> 11:59.983
No. I think
the Hindus have it right.

12:00.016 --> 12:01.787
Reincarnation, samsara.

12:01.820 --> 12:03.356
You come back
as any living thing,

12:03.389 --> 12:05.093
what would you come back as?

12:05.126 --> 12:06.530
I wouldn't want to come back.

12:06.563 --> 12:09.769
Um, I'm Team One Life,
one and done.

12:09.802 --> 12:11.038
-Oh.
-Mm-hmm.

12:11.071 --> 12:12.341
So you'd go out
like the Tibetans?

12:12.374 --> 12:14.211
Chop up your body,
scatter the pieces

12:14.244 --> 12:16.282
on the mountain
for the vultures.

12:16.315 --> 12:18.353
You'd just return to the earth
and all that jazz?

12:18.386 --> 12:21.192
A sky burial seems
unnecessarily gruesome.

12:21.225 --> 12:24.833
But, uh, I could get down
with how the Amazons do it.

12:24.866 --> 12:26.837
Cremation,

12:26.870 --> 12:28.941
then stirring your ashes
into soup for the whole tribe.

12:28.974 --> 12:31.278
Plus, you'd be giving back
to the community.

12:31.311 --> 12:33.349
(mechanical whirring)

12:33.382 --> 12:35.521
CHARLIE:
1,500 years ago in China,
a woman buried herself

12:35.554 --> 12:38.827
alive with her dead husband so
they could achieve immortality.

12:38.860 --> 12:40.263
That's a bit dramatic.

12:40.296 --> 12:43.369
That's true love.

12:43.402 --> 12:45.140
SAM:
Lord Nelson's body

12:45.173 --> 12:47.377
was shipped home
in a cask of brandy.

12:47.410 --> 12:50.417
The sailors even stole sips
along the voyage.

12:50.450 --> 12:52.254
Would you steal a sip?

12:52.287 --> 12:54.091
(laughing):
Um...

12:54.124 --> 12:56.530
Sure. Why not?

12:56.563 --> 12:59.001
Can't learn anything
if you don't try everything.

12:59.034 --> 13:02.240
I'm pretty adventurous, but, um,

13:02.273 --> 13:04.278
think I'd draw the line
at Dead Nelson juice.

13:04.311 --> 13:06.282
What's the most adventurous
thing you've ever eaten?

13:06.315 --> 13:08.419
Hmm.

13:11.325 --> 13:13.029
It's been a minute. Um...

13:13.062 --> 13:16.503
My boyfriend doesn't really
like to try new things,

13:16.536 --> 13:20.878
uh, so we pretty much
just stick to the basics.

13:20.911 --> 13:23.249
Well, just 'cause he doesn't
like something doesn't mean

13:23.282 --> 13:25.186
you can't experience it.

13:25.219 --> 13:28.226
Jesse thinks
carne asada is exotic.

13:28.259 --> 13:30.498
(laughing):
Oh, my God.

13:30.531 --> 13:33.002
-I'm gonna have to save you
from, your, uh...
-Hmm.

13:33.035 --> 13:34.371
your sad existence.

13:34.404 --> 13:36.208
-Oh, my...
-Jalapeño chips to the rescue!

13:36.241 --> 13:37.612
Free yourself!

13:37.645 --> 13:39.515
-Expand your horizons! (laughs)
-Stop!

13:40.918 --> 13:43.891
This guy had a lot of people
who loved him.

13:43.924 --> 13:48.066
Would your family do a whole
dog and pony show for you?

13:48.099 --> 13:51.338
Uh... no.

13:51.371 --> 13:53.977
They on board with your whole
obsession with death?

13:55.581 --> 13:57.552
I hope so.

13:57.585 --> 14:00.089
They're all dead.

14:01.125 --> 14:04.064
-I'm sorry.
-It's okay.

14:05.601 --> 14:07.638
I like talking about them.

14:11.011 --> 14:13.584
My Dad-- he was, um...

14:13.617 --> 14:17.124
he was such a stud.

14:17.157 --> 14:19.496
He'd taken us to Zion

14:19.529 --> 14:22.635
'cause he liked
these big, stupid rocks.

14:22.668 --> 14:25.340
My mom hated the outdoors.
She couldn't stand the heat,

14:25.373 --> 14:28.446
the bugs,
but she loved my dad.

14:28.479 --> 14:31.185
Sadie was a total
Daddy's girl.

14:31.218 --> 14:33.289
She'd follow him anywhere.

14:33.322 --> 14:34.659
DAD:
Charlie?

14:34.692 --> 14:36.195
Dad was telling
this dumb joke.

14:36.228 --> 14:37.430
I got a joke for you.
You ready, bud?

14:37.463 --> 14:38.934
CHARLIE:
His jokes were so corny.

14:38.967 --> 14:41.506
This one got me.
Something about a...

14:41.539 --> 14:44.278
a monkey and a hyena.

14:44.311 --> 14:45.548
DAD:
Chimpanzee.

14:45.581 --> 14:46.448
(laughing like monkey)

14:46.481 --> 14:48.352
(horn honking)

14:49.187 --> 14:50.591
(glass breaking)

14:50.624 --> 14:53.262
In a way, it was a blessing.

14:56.068 --> 14:58.574
I don't... I don't understand.

14:58.607 --> 15:00.343
Having such
a close brush with death

15:00.376 --> 15:02.347
brought everything
into clear focus.

15:02.380 --> 15:04.484
I saw how precious life is.

15:06.255 --> 15:09.361
And how we as the living
owe it to the dead

15:09.394 --> 15:11.198
to take care of them.

15:11.231 --> 15:13.335
And to live boldly.

15:18.379 --> 15:20.517
I know exactly how you feel.

15:21.586 --> 15:24.057
Did some drunk driver
take out your entire family

15:24.090 --> 15:26.228
as well in a blaze of glory?

15:32.575 --> 15:35.212
Trauma is, uh...

15:39.154 --> 15:41.626
It's complicated.

15:44.665 --> 15:46.736
It, um...

15:51.478 --> 15:54.250
It fucks with your... brain.

15:56.421 --> 15:59.360
Hey, I-I thought we were talking
about my dead family.

16:01.532 --> 16:03.670
I don't talk about mine, ever.

16:05.774 --> 16:08.513
Not with Jesse, not with, uh...

16:08.546 --> 16:10.650
well, anyone.

16:13.389 --> 16:15.426
But right now, I, um...

16:21.238 --> 16:23.408
I want to.

16:28.285 --> 16:30.156
(phone rings)

16:30.189 --> 16:32.595
Hmm.

16:32.628 --> 16:34.699
-Hey.
-JESSE: Hey, where are you?

16:34.732 --> 16:36.603
I've been stalling,
my parents are getting hungry.

16:36.636 --> 16:38.707
Shit.
No. Uh, um, I'm sorry.

16:38.740 --> 16:42.113
No.
I totally spaced. We...

16:42.146 --> 16:44.251
We're prepping for a service.

16:44.284 --> 16:47.324
Um... I'm leaving now, okay?

16:47.357 --> 16:48.727
I'll be... I'll be home in ten.

16:48.760 --> 16:51.031
All right, see you soon.

16:53.202 --> 16:55.173
Hey, I... I got to go.

16:55.206 --> 16:57.243
Um, Jesse's parents just
flew in from Cincinnati.

16:57.276 --> 16:59.716
-I just totally spaced.
-Don't worry about it.

16:59.749 --> 17:02.521
I can finish up here.

17:02.554 --> 17:04.726
Thank you.

17:04.759 --> 17:06.696
Oh, wait.

17:09.434 --> 17:11.438
You wanted to, uh,

17:11.471 --> 17:14.043
tell me something.

17:14.845 --> 17:16.850
I'll, um...

17:16.883 --> 17:19.120
I'll tell you later.

17:22.761 --> 17:24.798
(door closes)

17:26.134 --> 17:28.472
Hi. Sorry I'm late.

17:28.506 --> 17:30.242
How was the flight?

17:35.486 --> 17:37.524
(switch clicking)

17:40.429 --> 17:42.466
(glass breaking)

17:57.263 --> 17:59.233
(soft crunching)

18:00.670 --> 18:02.173
(woman screams)

18:04.411 --> 18:08.152
-(banging)
-(woman shrieks)

18:08.185 --> 18:10.791
(woman whimpering)

18:10.824 --> 18:12.293
(man grunts)

18:12.326 --> 18:15.400
No! No! No!

18:15.433 --> 18:17.672
(woman whimpering)

18:17.705 --> 18:18.740
GIRL:
Mama?

18:24.652 --> 18:26.722
It's okay, Mama.

18:27.725 --> 18:30.664
-(crying)
-It's-it's okay.

18:30.697 --> 18:33.402
-It's okay. It's okay.
-(crying)

18:33.435 --> 18:35.874
-It's okay. What is it?
-(crying)

18:37.845 --> 18:39.381
What is it?

18:39.414 --> 18:40.651
(crying)

18:40.684 --> 18:42.688
Uh, you always got a box
of these stashed,

18:42.721 --> 18:43.957
so I thought it'd be romantic.

18:43.990 --> 18:45.393
-Hey.
-(crying)

18:45.426 --> 18:47.463
